  "output": "---\n\n## Performance Analysis — BeerGame core engine\n\n**Scope:** Only Python core exists. No frontend, no DB, no FastAPI yet. React re-renders: N/A (Svelte, not React).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Memory leak — `incoming_orders` grows forever, never read\n\n`order_processor.py:72` appends to `upstream_ps.incoming_orders` every round. Nothing ever reads or trims it. After 26 rounds each player has 25 dead entries.\n\n```python\n# game.py:36 — this list accumulates and is never consumed\nincoming_orders: list[int] = Field(default_factory=list)\n```\n\n`accrue_costs`, `fulfill_orders`, `advance_shipments` — none of them touch `incoming_orders`. It's dead storage.\n\n**Fix:** Either remove `incoming_orders` from `PlayerState`, or clear it at round end:\n\n```python\n# order_processor.py — end of place_orders, before return\nfor ps in state.players.values():\n    ps.incoming_orders.clear()\n```\n\nOr remove the field entirely if it's not used for visibility/reporting.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Redundant double-iteration in `advance_shipments`\n\n`order_processor.py:7-13` iterates `incoming_shipments` twice per player per round:\n\n```python\n# pass 1\narrived = sum(s.quantity for s in ps.incoming_shipments if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1)\n# pass 2 — same list\nps.incoming_shipments = [\n    IncomingShipment(quantity=s.quantity, arrives_in_rounds=s.arrives_in_rounds - 1)\n    for s in ps.incoming_shipments\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds > 1\n]\n```\n\nAlso creates new `IncomingShipment` Pydantic objects for every surviving shipment — unnecessary allocation.\n\n**Fix — single pass, mutate in place:**\n\n```python\ndef advance_shipments(state: GameState) -> GameState:\n    for ps in state.players.values():\n        arrived = 0\n        survivors = []\n        for s in ps.incoming_shipments:\n            if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1:\n                arrived += s.quantity\n            else:\n                s.arrives_in_rounds -= 1  # mutate; Pydantic v2 allows this\n                survivors.append(s)\n        ps.inventory += arrived\n        ps.incoming_shipments = survivors\n    return state\n```\n\nHalves iterations, eliminates Pydantic object churn.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Import inside loop — `game_engine.py:33`\n\n```python\nfor role in ROLE_ORDER:\n    ...\n    for delay in range(1, cfg.shipping_delay + 1):\n        from core.models import IncomingShipment  # ← inside nested loop\n```\n\nPython caches imports after first load so this isn't catastrophic, but it's wrong style and adds dict-lookup overhead every iteration.\n\n**Fix:** Move to top of `game_engine.py` with the other imports.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `PlayerState.round_cost()` ignores config — correctness bug\n\n`game.py:41-42`:\n\n```python\ndef round_cost(self) -> float:\n    return self.inventory * HOLDING_COST_PER_UNIT + self.backlog * BACKLOG_COST_PER_UNIT\n```\n\nUses module-level constants, not config values. `accrue_costs` correctly uses `state.config.holding_cost` — so `round_cost()` diverges from actual accrual when config differs from defaults. Any reporting or AI player calling `round_cost()` gets wrong numbers.\n\n**Fix:**\n\n```python\n# Remove round_cost() from PlayerState — it can't see config.\n# Or pass config: GameConfig as argument.\ndef round_cost(self, config: GameConfig) -> float:\n    return self.inventory * config.holding_cost + self.backlog * config.backlog_cost\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Caching opportunity — `get_visible_state` / `model_dump`\n\n`game_engine.py:95`:\n\n```python\n\"incoming_shipments\": [s.model_dump() for s in ps.incoming_shipments],\n```\n\nCalled per WebSocket message per player per tick. At scale (many concurrent games), Pydantic serialization adds up. State only changes after `process_round()` — safe to cache until next round.\n\n**Future fix (when WebSocket layer exists):** Cache visible state per (game_id, role, round) and invalidate on round advance. Not urgent now with no API layer yet.\n\n---\n\n### Summary table\n\n| Issue | File | Severity | Type |\n|-------|------|----------|------|\n| `incoming_orders` never cleared | `game.py:36`, `order_processor.py:72` | Medium | Memory |\n| Double iteration + Pydantic alloc | `order_processor.py:7-13` | Low-Medium | CPU/Memory |\n| Import inside loop | `game_engine.py:33` | Low | Style/CPU |\n| `round_cost()` ignores config | `game.py:41` | High | **Correctness bug** |\n| `model_dump` per tick per player | `game_engine.py:95` | Low (now), Medium (at scale) | CPU |\n\nMost urgent fix: item 4 (`round_cost` correctness) + item 1 (accumulating dead data). Items 2-3 are trivial cleanup.\n",
